ation for the BaseTestRunnerTest, and it seems like the resources are only coming from the agent. However, the metadata at the top doesn’t include this information. The native tests may have generated a resource-config, but do they actually need these AssertJ resources? Existing tests appear to pass, and we do use assertThat. The resources are present in the agent output, but they don't seem relevant to the metadata. It’s a bit confusing!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Figuring out code tracing**\\n\\nI'm thinking about code testing and whether I can trace it effectively. It’s puzzling that I have native results passing even without AssertJ metadata. So, I wonder if the Gradle plugin generates some configuration. I know I need to write to a file, but I have to ensure that the class name is public and in a dedicated file. Maybe I could call `createUI` and `rerun` from that single file—it's worth considering!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_el4DJDp5CPejqwpkUQZgyEBy|fc_0bf745c2a1bd5e300169f90d62c1a88193be0017a2dc70f477", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/src/test/java/junit_junit/AwtuiTestRunnerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage junit_junit;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.awt.Frame;\nimport java.awt.List;\nimport java.awt.TextField;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Vector;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport junit.framework.TestCase;\nimport junit.framework.TestResult;\nimport junit.awtui.TestRunner;\n\npublic class AwtuiTestRunnerTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void createsUserInterfaceWithFrameIconFromRunnerResource() {\n        ExposedAwtTestRunner runner = new ExposedAwtTestRunner();\n        Frame frame = null;\n        try {\n            frame = runner.newUserInterface(ReloadableTestCase.class.getName());\n\n            assertThat(frame.getIconImage()).isNotNull();\n        } finally {\n            if (frame != null) {\n                frame.dispose();\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void rerunsSelectedTestCaseThroughStringConstructor() {\n        ReloadableTestCase.constructedNames.clear();\n        ReloadableTestCase.executedNames.clear();\n        ExposedAwtTestRunner runner = new ExposedAwtTestRunner();\n        ReloadableTestCase original = new ReloadableTestCase(\"testRecordsName\");\n        runner.prepareSelectedFailure(original);\n        runner.setLoading(false);\n\n        runner.rerun();\n\n        assertThat(ReloadableTestCase.constructedNames).containsExactly(\"testRecordsName\", \"testRecordsName\");\n        assertThat(ReloadableTestCase.executedNames).containsExactly(\"testRecordsName\");\n        assertThat(runner.statusText()).isEqualTo(original + \" was successful\");\n    }\n\n    public static class ReloadableTestCase extends TestCase {\n        static final java.util.List<String> constructedNames = new ArrayList<>();\n        static final java.util.List<String> executedNames = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        public ReloadableTestCase(String name) {\n            super(name);\n            constructedNames.add(name);\n        }\n\n        public void testRecordsName() {\n            executedNames.add(getName());\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static class ExposedAwtTestRunner extends TestRunner {\n        Frame newUserInterface(String suiteName) {\n            return createUI(suiteName);\n        }\n\n        void prepareSelectedFailure(TestCase testCase) {\n            fFailureList = new List(1);\n            fFailureList.add(testCase.toString());\n            fFailureList.select(0);\n            fFailedTests = new Vector();\n            fFailedTests.addElement(testCase);\n            fStatusLine = new TextField();\n        }\n\n        String statusText() {\n            return fStatusLine.getText();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected TestResult createTestResult() {\n            return new TestResult();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 703, "output": 1852, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36347, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777929551769, "responseId": "resp_0bf745c2a1bd5e300169f90d503d808193b0d188aa2f74a974"}}
